data: {"type":"response.output_item.done","item":{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcp_0b39566e17157695006a10ad0428c88195b8e411ea44164932","agent_reference":{"type":"agent_reference","name":"cs-e2e-tests-client","version":"1"},"response_id":"resp_0b39566e17157695006a10acff8fcc8195a8b0ec3aea2f0bb0","server_label":"FoundryLinda2","name":"DataAgent_Foundry_Linda","arguments":"{\"userQuestion\":\"Weather history in London, Ohio. Provide summary of historical weather events from the Weather table for London, OH (or Madison County, OH), including event types, dates, impacts (damage, injuries/deaths), and narratives.\"}","output":"Here is a summary of historical weather events recorded for the London, Ohio area (including Madison County, OH):\n\n1. Lake-Effect Snow (Jan 24-25, 2007)\n   - Damages: $100,000 in property, no crop damage.\n   - Impacts: No injuries or deaths.\n   - Narrative: Snow showers began January 24th and continued into the 25th, with the heaviest snow falling during the morning of the 25th. Accumulations ranged from 6 to 10 inches, with a maximum reported of 12.5 inches in Madison Township. Dozens of accidents reported due to the snow.\n\n2. Winter Storm (Feb 13-14, 2007, two overlapping reports)\n   - Damages: $40,000–$60,000 in property, no crop damage.\n   - Impacts: No injuries or deaths.\n   - Narrative: Snow started Feb 13th and increased in intensity. Reports of 8–13 inches of snow. Snow and winds continued through Feb 14th, with up to 17.5 inches in some locations. Significant travel impacts were reported due to heavy snow and drifting.\n\n3. Flooding (Mar 1-2, 2007 & Mar 14, 2007)\n   - Damages: $3,000 in property per event.\n   - Impacts: No injuries or deaths.\n   - Narrative: Several roads flooded and some creeks out of banks due to heavy rainfall after cold fronts. Roads closed and localized flooding across the county.\n\n4. Winter Weather (Dec 7, 2007)\n   - Damages: None reported.\n   - Impacts: No injuries or deaths.\n   - Narrative: Two inches of snow in London, 1.1 inches in Mount Sterling. Occasional light freezing rain and drizzle. No significant impacts noted.\n\nOverall, main impacts were property damage from snow or flooding. No injuries or deaths were reported in these events. The narratives emphasize heavy snow accumulation, challenging travel conditions, and occasional flooding from heavy rain.\n","status":"completed"},"output_index":1,"sequence_number":11}

